{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01UMCZPHh3dFnsqF5Q7eXkFT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI've successfully identified the bug. The issue is in `libyara/atoms.c` in the `_yr_atoms_extract_from_re` function. The test changes the `defects4cpp.lua` index to 102, which triggers test case 102 in `test-atoms.c` designed to test regex atom extraction with wildcards.\n\nWhen running this test with index 102, it fails because the atom extraction code doesn't properly copy all fields when updating the best atom.\n\n**ROOT CAUSE:** `libyara/atoms.c:1074` — The statement `best_atom.length = atom.length;` is missing from the `_yr_atoms_extract_from_re` function. This line was removed in commit ee2a4187 (\"buggy\"), breaking the fix from commit 46a54d2e. When a better atom quality is found (lines 1066-1076), the code copies the atom's bytes and mask to `best_atom`, but fails to copy its length field. This causes the atom extraction to use an incorrect/stale length value when processing regex patterns with wildcards like `{?? 11 22 33 ?? 55 66 }`, leading to incorrect atom matching and test assertion failures.\n\n**LOCAL FIX:** Insert `best_atom.length = atom.length;` as a new line after line 1073 (after the closing brace of the for loop copying bytes/masks) and before line 1075 (the `best_quality = quality;` assignment):\n\n```c\n              for (i = 0; i < atom.length; i++)\n              {\n                best_atom.bytes[i] = atom.bytes[i];\n                best_atom.mask[i] = atom.mask[i];\n                best_atom_re_nodes[i] = recent_re_nodes[i + shift];\n              }\n\n              best_atom.length = atom.length;  // <-- ADD THIS LINE\n              best_quality = quality;\n```\n\n**GLOBAL FIX:** Replace the manual field-by-field copy loop (lines 1068-1073) with a single `memcpy` operation on the entire `YR_ATOM` struct, similar to how it's done elsewhere in the codebase (e.g., at line 1035). This ensures all struct fields are copied atomically and prevents future bugs from missing fields:\n\n```c\nmemcpy(&best_atom, &atom, sizeof(atom));\nfor (i = 0; i < atom.length; i++)\n{\n  best_atom_re_nodes[i] = recent_re_nodes[i + shift];\n}\nbest_quality = quality;\n```\n\nThis structural change treats the atom as a single unit rather than requiring manual coordination of multiple field copies, making the code less error-prone and more maintainable."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":525,"cache_read_input_tokens":66688,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":525},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7368b365-f06b-4f99-b5a0-4ee22c892722","uuid":"ac82855d-394c-49d0-a0e7-0a36a97d21f0"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":118880,"duration_api_ms":72073,"num_turns":26,"result":"## Summary\n\nI've successfully identified the bug. The issue is in `libyara/atoms.c` in the `_yr_atoms_extract_from_re` function. The test changes the `defects4cpp.lua` index to 102, which triggers test case 102 in `test-atoms.c` designed to test regex atom extraction with wildcards.\n\nWhen running this test with index 102, it fails because the atom extraction code doesn't properly copy all fields when updating the best atom.\n\n**ROOT CAUSE:** `libyara/atoms.c:1074` — The statement `best_atom.length = atom.length;` is missing from the `_yr_atoms_extract_from_re` function. This line was removed in commit ee2a4187 (\"buggy\"), breaking the fix from commit 46a54d2e. When a better atom quality is found (lines 1066-1076), the code copies the atom's bytes and mask to `best_atom`, but fails to copy its length field. This causes the atom extraction to use an incorrect/stale length value when processing regex patterns with wildcards like `{?? 11 22 33 ?? 55 66 }`, leading to incorrect atom matching and test assertion failures.\n\n**LOCAL FIX:** Insert `best_atom.length = atom.length;` as a new line after line 1073 (after the closing brace of the for loop copying bytes/masks) and before line 1075 (the `best_quality = quality;` assignment):\n\n```c\n              for (i = 0; i < atom.length; i++)\n              {\n                best_atom.bytes[i] = atom.bytes[i];\n                best_atom.mask[i] = atom.mask[i];\n                best_atom_re_nodes[i] = recent_re_nodes[i + shift];\n              }\n\n              best_atom.length = atom.length;  // <-- ADD THIS LINE\n              best_quality = quality;\n```\n\n**GLOBAL FIX:** Replace the manual field-by-field copy loop (lines 1068-1073) with a single `memcpy` operation on the entire `YR_ATOM` struct, similar to how it's done elsewhere in the codebase (e.g., at line 1035). This ensures all struct fields are copied atomically and prevents future bugs from missing fields:\n\n```c\nmemcpy(&best_atom, &atom, sizeof(atom));\nfor (i = 0; i < atom.length; i++)\n{\n  best_atom_re_nodes[i] = recent_re_nodes[i + shift];\n}\nbest_quality = quality;\n```\n\nThis structural change treats the atom as a single unit rather than requiring manual coordination of multiple field copies, making the code less error-prone and more maintainable.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"7368b365-f06b-4f99-b5a0-4ee22c892722","total_cost_usd":0.21047055000000006,"usage":{"input_tokens":273,"cache_creation_input_tokens":32745,"cache_read_input_tokens":1327273,"output_tokens":7091,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":32745,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":8,"output_tokens":754,"cache_read_input_tokens":66688,"cache_creation_input_tokens":525,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":525},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":1267,"outputTokens":7109,"cacheReadInputTokens":1327273,"cacheCreationInputTokens":32745,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.21047055000000006,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"1f399cbe-7a48-40e1-82af-10170486d45d"}
